race.comment: MISS MAZERATI (7) returns from a five-month spell. Peaked last prep with a win in a Class 3 which is excellent form for a race of this quality. Will be better next time but still right in the mix. SIGLO DE ORO (8) bolted in two back to collect his long-awaited maiden win then didn't measure up last time, both runs coming on the Gold Coast Poly. Not the most reliable conveyance - each-way chance. EAGLE'S FIRE (2) has been poor at his last couple, coinciding with a step up to 1100m. Must be a query at this trip but in a race that lacks depth he can sneak into the money. CARDSHARP (5) resumes and has been in the money at three of four first-up runs so must be respected.
